  "prompt": "Is the Tamil language older than Sanskrit? How old is it when compared to all other languages of the world?",
  "response": "The Tamil language is considered one of the oldest languages in the world, with a rich literary tradition that dates back over 2,000 years. It is believed to have originated around the 3rd century BCE, although some scholars argue that its roots go even further back.\n\nSanskrit, another ancient language, has a literary tradition that also dates back over 3,000 years, with the earliest texts, such as the Rigveda, being composed around 1500 BCE. Therefore, Sanskrit is generally considered older in terms of documented literary history.\n\nWhen comparing Tamil to all other languages in the world, it stands out as one of the ancient classical languages with a continuous literary tradition. Other ancient languages include Sumerian, Egyptian, Akkadian, Greek, and Chinese, each with their own historical timelines and contributions to human civilization.\n\nOverall, while Tamil is incredibly old and significant, Sanskrit is typically considered older in terms of the earliest recorded texts. Both languages have contributed immensely to the cultural and literary heritage of humanity.",
